---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { tools, verticals } from '../lib/data';
import useCasesData from '../data/use_cases.json';

const toolCount = tools.length;
const verticalCount = verticals.length;
const useCaseCount = (useCasesData.use_cases as unknown[]).length;

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'About', url: '/about/' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="About WrenchStack"
  description="WrenchStack is the trades software directory — connecting field service businesses with the right software, and software vendors with the right buyers."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">

    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 md:text-5xl">
        The trades software directory.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        WrenchStack connects trades and field service businesses with the software they need — and helps software vendors reach the contractors actively shopping for it.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-12 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">{toolCount}+</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Software platforms tracked</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">{verticalCount}</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Trades verticals covered</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">600+</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Indexed comparison pages</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">

      <h2>For contractors and field service operators</h2>

      <p>
        Picking the right software shouldn't take weeks of demos and sales calls. WrenchStack organizes the trades software market around the questions you actually ask — by team size, vertical, integration needs, and budget — so you can shortlist three real options in 15 minutes instead of three weeks.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="/tools/">{toolCount}+ tool reviews</a></strong> with verified pricing, feature breakdowns, and honest limitations</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/compare/">~480 head-to-head comparisons</a></strong> — any two tools that share a vertical, side-by-side</li>
        <li><strong>{verticalCount} vertical landing pages</strong> with ranked picks for HVAC, plumbing, electrical, roofing, landscaping, cleaning, pest control, and more</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/best-software-for/">{useCaseCount} buyer guides</a></strong> matched to specific situations — solo contractor, growing team, QuickBooks-heavy shop, insurance restoration roofer</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/pricing/">Pricing comparison pages</a></strong> per vertical, sorted cheapest first</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/quiz/">A matching quiz</a></strong> that returns three ranked picks in 60 seconds</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/roi-calculator/">An ROI calculator</a></strong> for projecting payback at your team size</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/migrate/">Migration guides</a></strong> if you're switching between platforms</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>For software vendors and partnership teams</h2>

      <p>
        WrenchStack reaches contractors at the moment they're actively shopping for software — long-tail organic search ("best HVAC software for solo contractor," "Jobber vs Housecall Pro," "ServiceTitan alternatives"). High intent, high purchase readiness, no display ads or generic banner placement competing for their attention.
      </p>

      <p>
        We work with vendors through affiliate partnerships rather than paid placements. Rankings are produced by a methodology that values your product on equal footing with competitors — no pay-to-rank, no preferred-vendor tier. The trade-off: when you rank well on WrenchStack, the buyers reading it know the ranking was earned, which converts better than sponsored content ever does.
      </p>

      <p>
        See the <a href="/affiliate-programs/">affiliate programs we work with</a> for the current partner list. To inquire about a partnership, reach out at <a href="mailto:partners@wrenchstack.com">partners@wrenchstack.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>How rankings work</h2>

      <p>
        Every tool carries a <strong>WrenchStack Score (0–10)</strong> calculated from four weighted factors:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Vertical fit (40%)</strong> — how well the tool is built for the specific trade being searched</li>
        <li><strong>Aggregated user ratings (30%)</strong> — averaged G2 + Capterra scores</li>
        <li><strong>Pricing transparency (10%)</strong> — public tier pricing beats custom-quote opacity</li>
        <li><strong>Feature depth + integration coverage (20%)</strong> — does the tool actually do the work, and does it connect to the tools you already use</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Full breakdown on the <a href="/methodology/">methodology page</a>. The ranking algorithm has no knowledge of affiliate commission rates — payouts don't move the order.
      </p>

      <h2>Who runs WrenchStack</h2>

      <p>
        WrenchStack is built and operated by <strong>Bilal Elhomsi</strong>, an entrepreneur with 15+ years of operating experience across hospitality, retail, construction, manufacturing, and consulting — and now software. Editorial focus is the field service software market globally.
      </p>

      <h2>How we make money</h2>

      <p>
        Affiliate commissions. When you sign up to a platform through one of our links, the vendor pays a referral fee from their customer acquisition budget. You pay the same price as buying direct. See the <a href="/disclosure/">disclosure page</a> for the full breakdown.
      </p>

      <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>General / corrections:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@wrenchstack.com">hello@wrenchstack.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Vendor partnerships:</strong> <a href="mailto:partners@wrenchstack.com">partners@wrenchstack.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Press / media:</strong> <a href="mailto:press@wrenchstack.com">press@wrenchstack.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        See the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> for direct links to each inbox.
      </p>

    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
